subtitleNullable: Pre-trained VGGNet models on the MNIST and Fashion_MNIST datasets
descriptionNullable:
VGG16 is object detection and classification algorithm which is able to classify 1000 images of 1000 different categories with 92.7% accuracy. It is one of the popular algorithms for image classification and is easy to use with transfer learning.
![](https://www.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/kaggle-user-content/o/inbox%2F17836414%2Fdf7310ffc49d3310b8f064cb6a4cf0fb%2Farchitecture.png?generation=1700739119862206&alt=media)

This dataset consists of VGG-16 models which are pre-trained on the MNIST (http://yann.lecun.com/exdb/mnist/) and the Fashion MNIST (https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/zalando-research/fashionmnist) datasets getting a classification accuracy of 99% and 92% respectively.

The notebook containing the code to train the model is given here - https://www.kaggle.com/code/shreyasi2002/vgg16-on-mnist-and-fashion-mnist
